revision.text:
{{Year in Sri Lanka|1993}}

The following lists events that happened during '''[[1993]] in [[Sri Lanka]]'''.

==Incumbents==
*[[President of Sri Lanka|President]]: [[Ranasinghe Premadasa]]

==Events==
* [[Lalith Athulathmudali]], the former Cabinet Minister of Trade, National Security, Agriculture, Education and Deputy Minister of Defence of Sri Lanka was killed at 8:10 p.m. Sri Lanka Time (2.10 p.m. UTC) on 23 April 1993 in [[Kirulapana]].<ref name="nytt">{{cite news | url= https://www.nytimes.com/1993/04/24/world/sri-lanka-opposition-leader-slain-at-rally.html?src=pm| title=Sri Lanka Opposition Leader Slain at Rally| publisher=[[The New York Times]] | accessdate=2011-06-09| date=April 24, 1993}}</ref>
* The [[Jaffna lagoon massacre]] occurred on January 2, 1993, when a Sri Lankan Navy Motor Gun Boat and a number of smaller speed boats intercepted a number of boats transporting people between the south and north shores of the Jaffna Lagoon in the Northern province in Sri Lanka, and attacked them under the glare of a spot light. Roughly 100 civilians and militants were killed.  <ref name=ai/><ref name=HRDC>{{cite book | last=Olsen | first=Bendigt | title= Human Rights in Developing Countries - Yearbook | date=1994 | publisher= [[Springer Science+Business Media|Springer]] |isbn=90-6544-845-4}} p.368</ref><ref name=ai>{{cite web|last= |first= |authorlink= |title=Amnesty International Report 1994 |work= |publisher=[[Amnesty International]] |date=1994 |url=http://www.unhcr.org/home/RSDCOI/3ae6a9f444.html |accessdate=2007-08-14 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120313212044/http://www.unhcr.org/home/RSDCOI/3ae6a9f444.html |archivedate=March 13, 2012 }}</ref><ref name=uthr>{{cite web   | last = Hoole   | first = Rajan   | authorlink = Rajan Hoole  | title = Feature: Massacre in the Jaffna Lagoon |  publisher = [[University Teachers for Human Rights]]   | date =   | url = http://www.uthr.org/Reports/Report10/chapter0.htm | accessdate = 2007-08-14 }}</ref><ref name=Island>{{cite news   | last = Fernando  | first = Shamindra  | coauthors =  | title = Navy demolishes Tiger boats | publisher = The Island  | date = January 5, 1993}}</ref>
*The [[Battle of Pooneryn]] was a battle fought on 11 November 1993 for the town of Pooneryn.<ref name="The Sunday Times Situation Report">{{cite web|url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/961013/sitrep.html|title=The Sunday Times Situation Report|publisher=Sundaytimes.lk|accessdate=6 October 2014}}</ref>
*Ranasinghe Premadasa was assassinated on 1 May 1993, during a [[May day]] rally, by an [[LTTE]] suicide bomber. Little more than a week before, Lalith Athulathmudali had also been assassinated.<ref name=NYT19930501>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1993/05/02/world/suicide-bomber-kills-president-of-sri-lanka.html?pagewanted=1|title=Suicide Bomber Kills President of Sri Lanka|first=Edward|last=Gargan|date=2 May 1993|publisher=New York Times}}</ref>

