68 Excavations at Tell Ta'annek |url= https://www.jstor.org/stable/1356432 |url-access=registration |access-date= 2018-06-11 |journal= Bulletin of the American Schools of Oriental Research |volume= |number= 195 |pages= 2–49 |publisher= The American Schools of Oriental Research |jstor= 1356432 |doi= 10.2307/1356432 }}</ref> {{Coord|32|31|15|N|35|13|11|E|type:city|display=inline}}<ref name="Kennedy_2013" />{{rp|509}} | |- | תפוח | tpwḥ | [[Tappuah of Judah|Tappuah]] [of Judah] | {{Strong-number|H8599|H|8599}} | Joshua (12:17?;) 15:34 | 2 or 1 | Judah ("in the valley"; important cities: Eshtaol, Zoreah, Engannim, Tappuah, Jarmuth, Adullam, Socoh 1, Azekah) | | |- | תפוח | tpwḥ | [[Tappuah of Ephraim|Tappuah]] [of Ephraim] | {{Strong-number|H8599|H|8599}} | Joshua (12:17?;) 16:8; 17:8 | 4 or 3 | Ephraim (northern border of Ephraim, located between Ephraim and Manasseh's territories) | | = En-Tappuah (H5887) ? |- | תראלה | trʾlh | Taralah | {{Strong-number|H8634|H|8634}} | Joshua 18:27 | 1 | Benjamin (group B; important cities: Gibeon, Ramah, Mizpeh, Jerusalem) | | |- | תרצה | trṣh | [[Tirzah (ancient city)|Tirzah]] | {{Strong-number|H8656|H|8656}} | Joshua 12:24 | 14 | ? (a king of this city was defeated by Joshua) | ?<ref name="Laughlin_2006">{{cite book |author1-last= Laughlin |author1-first= John Charles Hugh |year=2006 |url= https://books.google.pl/books?id=dUB048ItN8AC |url-access= limited |title= Fifty Major Cities of the Bible: From Dan to Beersheba |publisher= Routledge |isbn= 9780415223157 |archive-url= |archive-date= }}</ref>{{rp|116}} Tell el-Far'ah (North)<ref>{{cite journal |last1= de Vaux |first1= Roland |author-link1= Roland de Vaux |orig-year= 1956 |year= 2013 |title= The Excavations at Tell El-Far‘ah and the Site of Ancient Tirzah |url= https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1179/peq.1956.88.2.125 |url-access= subscription |access-date= 2018-05-29 |journal= Palestine Exploration Quarterly |volume= 88 |issue= 2 |pages= 125–140 |doi= 10.1179/peq.1956.88.2